<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 8PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
<A HREF="#V432483_10K_HTM_TOC">
	TABLE OF CONTENTS
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	investment in our portfolio. In connection with our valuation process, MC Advisors reviews these investment ratings on a quarterly basis, and our Board reviews and affirms such ratings. A definition of the rating system follows:
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
</P>
<EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<A NAME="FIS_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE_6"></A>
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="554" STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN: TEXT-TOP; TEXT-INDENT:0PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: -15PT; *MARGIN-TOP: -20PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
<TR>
<TD>
<IMG HEIGHT="1" SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/03/04/0001144204-16-085951_SPACER.GIF" WIDTH="72">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 12PX; VERTICAL-ALIGN: BOTTOM; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; BORDER-BOTTOM: NONE">
<!-- GUTTER -->
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD>
<IMG HEIGHT="1" SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/03/04/0001144204-16-085951_SPACER.GIF" WIDTH="466">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
<TD STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: NORMAL; VERTICAL-ALIGN: BOTTOM; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; FONT-SIZE: 8PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; BORDER-BOTTOM: 1PT SOLID BLACK" ROWSPAN=1 COLSPAN=1>
	Investment Performance Risk Rating
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 12PX; VERTICAL-ALIGN: BOTTOM; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; BORDER-BOTTOM: NONE" ROWSPAN=1>
<!-- GUTTER -->
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT: NORMAL; VERTICAL-ALIGN: BOTTOM; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; FONT-SIZE: 8PT; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; BORDER-BOTTOM: 1PT SOLID BLACK" ROWSPAN=1 COLSPAN=1>
	Summary Description
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
<TD STYLE="PADDING-LEFT: 10PT; TEXT-INDENT: -10PT" ROWSPAN=1 COLSPAN=1>
	Grade 1
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 12PX; VERTICAL-ALIGN: BOTTOM; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; BORDER-BOTTOM: NONE" ROWSPAN=1>
<!-- GUTTER -->
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD ROWSPAN=1 COLSPAN=1 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	Includes investments exhibiting the least amount of risk in our portfolio. The issuer is performing above expectations or the issuer&#146;s operating trends and risk factors are generally positive.
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
<TD STYLE="PADDING-LEFT: 10PT; TEXT-INDENT: -10PT" ROWSPAN=1 COLSPAN=1>
	Grade 2
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 12PX; VERTICAL-ALIGN: BOTTOM; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; BORDER-BOTTOM: NONE" ROWSPAN=1>
<!-- GUTTER -->
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD ROWSPAN=1 COLSPAN=1 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	Includes investments exhibiting an acceptable level of risk that is similar to the risk at the time of origination. The issuer is generally performing as expected or the risk factors are neutral to positive.
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
<TD STYLE="PADDING-LEFT: 10PT; TEXT-INDENT: -10PT" ROWSPAN=1 COLSPAN=1>
	Grade 3
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 12PX; VERTICAL-ALIGN: BOTTOM; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; BORDER-BOTTOM: NONE" ROWSPAN=1>
<!-- GUTTER -->
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD ROWSPAN=1 COLSPAN=1 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	Includes investments performing below expectations and indicates that the investment&#146;s risk has increased somewhat since origination. The issuer may be out of compliance with debt covenants; however, scheduled loan payments are generally not past due.
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
<TD STYLE="PADDING-LEFT: 10PT; TEXT-INDENT: -10PT" ROWSPAN=1 COLSPAN=1>
	Grade 4
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 12PX; VERTICAL-ALIGN: BOTTOM; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; BORDER-BOTTOM: NONE" ROWSPAN=1>
<!-- GUTTER -->
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD ROWSPAN=1 COLSPAN=1 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	Includes an issuer performing materially below expectations and indicates that the issuer&#146;s risk has increased materially since origination. In addition to the issuer being generally out of compliance with debt covenants, scheduled loan payments may be past due (but generally not more than six months past due). For grade 4 investments, we intend to increase monitoring of the issuer.
</TD>
</TR>
<TR STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
<TD STYLE="PADDING-LEFT: 10PT; TEXT-INDENT: -10PT" ROWSPAN=1 COLSPAN=1>
	Grade 5
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 12PX; VERTICAL-ALIGN: BOTTOM; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; BORDER-BOTTOM: NONE" ROWSPAN=1>
<!-- GUTTER -->
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD ROWSPAN=1 COLSPAN=1 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	Indicates that the issuer is performing substantially below expectations and the investment risk has substantially increased since origination. Most or all of the debt covenants are out of compliance or payments are substantially delinquent. Investments graded 5 are not anticipated to be repaid in full, and we will reduce the fair market value of the loan to the amount we expect to recover.
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Our investment performance ratings do not constitute any ratings of investments by a nationally recognized statistical rating organization or represent or reflect any third-party assessment of any of our investments.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	In the event of a delinquency or a decision to rate a loan grade 4 or grade 5, the applicable analyst, in consultation with a member of the investment committee, develops an action plan. Such a plan may require a meeting with the borrower&#146;s management or the lender group to discuss reasons for the default and the steps management is undertaking to address the under-performance, as well as required amendments and waivers that may be required. In the event of a dramatic deterioration of a credit, MC Advisors forms a team or engages outside advisors to analyze, evaluate and take further steps to preserve its value in the
	credit. In this regard, we would expect to explore all options, including in a private equity sponsored investment, assuming certain responsibilities for the private equity sponsor or a formal sale of the business with oversight of the sale process by us. Several of Monroe Capital&#146;s professionals are experienced in running debt work-out transactions and bankruptcies.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	The following table shows the distribution of our investments on the 1 to 5 investment performance rating scale at fair value as of December 31, 2015 (dollars in thousands):
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">

<H1 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 9PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	MANAGEMENT AND OTHER AGREEMENTS
</H1>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	MC Advisors is located at 311 South Wacker Drive, Suite 6400, Chicago, Illinois 60606. MC Advisors is a registered investment adviser under the Advisers Act. Subject to the overall supervision of our Board and in accordance with the 1940 Act, MC Advisors manages our day-to-day operations and provides investment advisory services to us. Under the terms of the Investment Advisory and Management Agreement, MC Advisors:
</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
<TR STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 21PX">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 24PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	&#149;
</TD>
<TD STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	determines the composition of our portfolio, the nature and timing of the changes to our portfolio and the manner of implementing such changes;
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
<TR STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 21PX">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 24PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	&#149;
</TD>
<TD STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	assists us in determining what securities we purchase, retain or sell;
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
<TR STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 21PX">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 24PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	&#149;
</TD>
<TD STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	identifies, evaluates and negotiates the structure of the investments we make (including performing due diligence on our prospective portfolio companies); and
</TD>

<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
<TR STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 21PX">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 24PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	&#149;
</TD>
<TD STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	executes, closes, services and monitors the investments we make.

<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	MC Advisors&#146; services under the Investment Advisory and Management Agreement are not exclusive, and it is free to furnish similar services to other entities so long as its services to us are not impaired.
</P>
<H3 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 5PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Management and Incentive Fee
</H3>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Under the Investment Advisory and Management Agreement with MC Advisors and subject to the overall supervision of our Board, MC Advisors provides investment advisory services to us. For providing these services, MC Advisors receives a fee from us, consisting of two components&nbsp;&#151;&nbsp;a base management fee and an incentive fee. The base management fee is calculated at an annual rate of 1.75% of average invested assets (calculated as total assets excluding cash) and is payable quarterly in arrears.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	The incentive fee consists of two parts. The first part is calculated and payable quarterly in arrears based on our pre-incentive fee net investment income for the preceding quarter subject to a total return requirement. Pre-incentive fee net investment income means interest income, dividend income and any other income (including any other fees such as commitment, origination, structuring, diligence and consulting fees or other fees that we receive from portfolio companies but excluding fees for providing managerial assistance) accrued during the calendar quarter, minus operating expenses for the quarter (including the base
	management fee, any expenses payable under our administration agreement between an affiliate of Monroe Capital and MC Advisors (the &#147;Administration Agreement&#148;) and any interest expense and dividends paid on any outstanding preferred stock, but excluding the incentive fee). Pre-incentive fee net investment income includes, in the case of investments with a deferred interest feature such as market discount, debt instruments with PIK interest, preferred stock with PIK dividends and zero-coupon securities, accrued income that we have not yet received in cash. MC Advisors is not under any obligation to reimburse us for any part of the incentive fee it received that was based on accrued interest that we never actually receive.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	The foregoing incentive fee is subject to a total return requirement, which provides that no incentive fee in respect of our pre-incentive fee net investment income will be payable except to the extent 20.0% of the cumulative net increase in net assets resulting from operations over the then-current and 11 preceding quarters exceeds the cumulative incentive fees accrued and/or paid for the 11 preceding quarters. Therefore, any
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="WIDTH: 708PX; TEXT-INDENT:0PX; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; COLOR: BLACK; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; TEXT-DECORATION: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 12PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	13
</P>
<HR ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 708PX; HEIGHT: 2PX; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
<DIV ID="PN" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</DIV>
<A NAME="eolPage16"></A>
<DIV ID="HDR">
	&nbsp;
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH: 708PX; BORDER-TOP: 1PT WHITE SOLID; BORDER-BOTTOM: 1PT WHITE SOLID; BORDER-RIGHT: 1PT WHITE SOLID; BORDER-LEFT: 1PT WHITE SOLID; PADDING-TOP: 9PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 9PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 3PT; PADDING-LEFT:6PT; MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 8PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
<A HREF="#V432483_10K_HTM_TOC">
	TABLE OF CONTENTS
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	ordinary income incentive fee that is payable in a calendar quarter will be limited to the lesser of (i) 20% of the amount by which our pre-incentive fee net investment income for such calendar quarter exceeds the 2% hurdle described below, subject to the &#147;catch-up&#148; provision, and (ii) (x) 20% of the cumulative net increase in net assets resulting from operations for the then current and 11 preceding calendar quarters minus (y) the cumulative incentive fees accrued and/or paid for the 11 preceding calendar quarters. For the foregoing purpose, the &#147;cumulative net increase in net assets resulting from
	operations&#148; is the amount, if positive, of the sum of our pre-incentive fee net investment income, base management fees, realized gains and losses and unrealized appreciation and depreciation for the then-current and 11 preceding calendar quarters.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Pre-incentive fee net investment income does not include any realized capital gains, realized capital losses or unrealized capital appreciation or depreciation. If any distributions from portfolio companies are characterized as a return of capital, such returns of capital would affect the capital gains incentive fee to the extent a gain or loss is realized. Because of the structure of the incentive fee, it is possible that we may pay an incentive fee in a quarter where we incur a loss. For example, if we receive pre-incentive fee net investment income in excess of the hurdle rate (as defined below) for a quarter, we will pay
	the applicable incentive fee even if we have incurred a loss in that quarter due to realized and unrealized capital losses.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Pre-incentive fee net investment income, expressed as a rate of return on the value of our net assets (defined as total assets less indebtedness and before taking into account any incentive fees payable during the period) at the end of the immediately preceding calendar quarter, is compared to a fixed &#147;hurdle rate&#148; of 2% per quarter (8% annually). If market interest rates rise, we may be able to invest our funds in debt instruments that provide for a higher return, which would increase our pre-incentive fee net investment income and make it easier for MC Advisors to surpass the fixed hurdle rate and receive an
	incentive fee based on such net investment income.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	We pay MC Advisors an incentive fee with respect to our pre-incentive fee net investment income in each calendar quarter as follows:
</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
<TR STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 21PX">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 24PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	&#149;
</TD>
<TD STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	no incentive fee in any calendar quarter in which the pre-incentive fee net investment income does not exceed the hurdle rate of 2% (8% annually);
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
<TR STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 21PX">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 24PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	&#149;
</TD>
<TD STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	100% of our pre-incentive fee net investment income with respect to that portion of such pre-incentive fee net investment income, if any, that exceeds the hurdle rate but is less than 2.5% in any calendar quarter. We refer to this portion of our pre-incentive fee net investment income (which exceeds the hurdle rate but is less than 2.5%) as the &#147;catch-up&#148; provision. The catch-up is meant to provide MC Advisors with 20% of the pre-incentive fee net investment income as if a hurdle rate did not apply if this net investment income exceeds 2.5% in any calendar quarter; and
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
<TR STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 21PX">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 24PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	&#149;
</TD>
<TD STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	20% of the amount of our pre-incentive fee net investment income, if any, that exceeds 2.5% in any calendar quarter.
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	These calculations are adjusted for any share issuances or repurchases during the quarter.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	The following is a graphical representation of the calculation of the income-related portion of the incentive fee:
</P>
<H1 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 9PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Quarterly Incentive Fee Based on Pre-Incentive Fee Net Investment Income

	&nbsp;
<BR>
	Pre-incentive fee net investment income (expressed as a percentage of the value of net assets)
</H1>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">

<H1 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 9PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Percentage of pre-incentive fee net investment income allocated to income-related portion

	of incentive fee
</H1>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	These calculations will be appropriately prorated for any period of less than three months and adjusted for any share issuances or repurchases during the current quarter.
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="WIDTH: 708PX; TEXT-INDENT:0PX; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; COLOR: BLACK; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; TEXT-DECORATION: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 12PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	14

<HR ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 708PX; HEIGHT: 2PX; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
<DIV ID="PN" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</DIV>
<A NAME="eolPage17"></A>
<DIV ID="HDR">
	&nbsp;
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH: 708PX; BORDER-TOP: 1PT WHITE SOLID; BORDER-BOTTOM: 1PT WHITE SOLID; BORDER-RIGHT: 1PT WHITE SOLID; BORDER-LEFT: 1PT WHITE SOLID; PADDING-TOP: 9PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 9PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 3PT; PADDING-LEFT:6PT; MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 8PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
<A HREF="#V432483_10K_HTM_TOC">
	TABLE OF CONTENTS
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	The second part of the incentive fee is a capital gains incentive fee that is determined and payable in arrears as of the end of each fiscal year (or upon termination of the investment advisory and management agreement, as of the termination date), and equals 20% of our realized capital gains as of the end of the fiscal year. In determining the capital gains incentive fee payable to MC Advisors, we calculate the cumulative aggregate realized capital gains and cumulative aggregate realized capital losses since our inception, and the aggregate unrealized capital depreciation as of the date of the calculation, as applicable, with
	respect to each of the investments in our portfolio. For this purpose, cumulative aggregate realized capital gains, if any, equals the sum of the differences between the net sales price of each investment, when sold, and the amortized cost of such investment. Cumulative aggregate realized capital losses equals the sum of the amounts by which the net sales price of each investment, when sold, is less than the amortized cost of such investment since our inception. Aggregate unrealized capital depreciation equals the sum of the difference, if negative, between the valuation of each investment as of the applicable calculation date and the amortized cost of such investment. At the end of the applicable year, the amount of capital gains that serves as the basis for our calculation of the capital gains incentive fee equals the cumulative aggregate realized capital gains less cumulative aggregate realized capital losses, less aggregate unrealized capital depreciation, with respect to our
	portfolio of investments. If this number is positive at the end of such year, then the capital gains incentive fee for such year equals 20% of such amount, less the aggregate amount of any capital gains incentive fees paid in respect of our portfolio in all prior years.
</P>
<H2 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 5PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Examples of Quarterly Incentive Fee Calculation
</H2>
<H2 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 5PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Example 1: Income Related Portion of Incentive Fee before Total Return Requirement Calculation
</H2>
<H3 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 5PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 24PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Alternative 1
</H3>
<H4 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 24PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Assumptions
</H4>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Investment income (including interest, dividends, fees, etc.) = 1.25%
<BR>
	Hurdle rate
<SUP>
	(1)
</SUP>
	= 2%
<BR>
	Management fee
<SUP>
	(2)
</SUP>
	= 0.4375%
<BR>
	Other expenses (legal, accounting, custodian, transfer agent, etc.) = 0.2%
<BR>
	Pre-incentive fee net investment income
<BR>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(investment income&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;(management fee + other expenses)) = 0.6125%
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Pre-incentive fee net investment income does not exceed hurdle rate, therefore there is no income-related incentive fee.
</P>
<H3 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 5PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 24PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Alternative 2
</H3>
<H4 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 24PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Assumptions
</H4>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Investment income (including interest, dividends, fees, etc.) = 3.0%
<BR>
	Hurdle rate
<SUP>
	(1)
</SUP>
	= 2%
<BR>
	Management fee
<SUP>
	(2)
</SUP>
	= 0.4375%
<BR>
	Other expenses (legal, accounting, custodian, transfer agent, etc.) = 0.2%
<BR>
	Pre-incentive fee net investment income
<BR>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(investment income&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;(management fee + other expenses)) = 2.3625%
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Incentive fee&nbsp;=&nbsp;100% &#215; Pre-incentive fee net investment income (subject to &#147;catch-up&#148;)
<SUP>
	(3)
</SUP>
<BR>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=&nbsp;100% &#215; (2.3625%&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;2%)
<BR>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=&nbsp;0.3625%
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Pre-incentive fee net investment income exceeds the hurdle rate, but does not fully satisfy the &#147;catch-up&#148; provision, therefore the income-related portion of the incentive fee is 0.3625%.
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="WIDTH: 708PX; TEXT-INDENT:0PX; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; COLOR: BLACK; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; TEXT-DECORATION: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 12PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	15
</P>
<HR ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 708PX; HEIGHT: 2PX; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
<DIV ID="PN" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</DIV>
<A NAME="eolPage18"></A>
<DIV ID="HDR">
	&nbsp;
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH: 708PX; BORDER-TOP: 1PT WHITE SOLID; BORDER-BOTTOM: 1PT WHITE SOLID; BORDER-RIGHT: 1PT WHITE SOLID; BORDER-LEFT: 1PT WHITE SOLID; PADDING-TOP: 9PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 9PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 3PT; PADDING-LEFT:6PT; MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 8PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">
<A HREF="#V432483_10K_HTM_TOC">
	TABLE OF CONTENTS
</A>
</P>
<H3 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 5PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 24PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Alternative 3
</H3>
<H4 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 24PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Assumptions
</H4>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Investment income (including interest, dividends, fees, etc.) = 3.5%
<BR>
	Hurdle rate
<SUP>
	(1)
</SUP>
	= 2%
<BR>
	Management fee
<SUP>
	(2)
</SUP>
	= 0.4375%
<BR>
	Other expenses (legal, accounting, custodian, transfer agent, etc.) = 0.2%
<BR>
	Pre-incentive fee net investment income
<BR>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(investment income&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;(management fee + other expenses)) = 2.8625%
<BR>
	Incentive fee = 100% &#215; Pre-incentive fee net investment income (subject to &#147;catch-up&#148;)
<SUP>
	(3)
</SUP>
<BR>
	Incentive fee = 100% &#215; &#147;catch-up&#148; + (20% &#215; (Pre-incentive fee net investment income&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;2.5%))
<BR>
	&#147;Catch-up&#148;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;= 2.5%&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;2%
<BR>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;= 0.5%
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Incentive fee&nbsp;=&nbsp;(100% &#215; 0.5%) + (20% &#215; (2.8625%&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;2.5%))
<BR>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;= 0.5% + (20% &#215; 0.3625%)
<BR>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;= 0.5% + 0.0725%
<BR>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;= 0.5725%
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Pre-incentive fee net investment income exceeds the hurdle rate, and fully satisfies the &#147;catch-up&#148; provision, therefore the income related portion of the incentive fee is 0.56%.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 1PX">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/03/04/0001144204-16-085951_LINE.GIF" STYLE="WIDTH: 72PX; HEIGHT: 1PT">
</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
<TR STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 1PX">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	(1)
</TD>
<TD STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	Represents 8.0% annualized hurdle rate.
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
<TR STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 1PX">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	(2)
</TD>
<TD STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	Represents 1.75% annualized base management fee.
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
<TR STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 1PX">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	(3)
</TD>
<TD STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	The &#147;catch-up&#148; provision is intended to provide our investment advisor with an incentive fee of 20% on all pre-incentive fee net investment income as if a hurdle rate did not apply when our net investment income exceeds 2.5% in any fiscal quarter.
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<H2 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 5PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Example 2: Income Portion of Incentive Fee with Total Return Requirement Calculation:
</H2>
<H3 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 5PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 24PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Assumptions
</H3>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Hurdle rate
<SUP>
	(1)
</SUP>
	= 2%
<BR>
	Management fee
<SUP>
	(2)
</SUP>
	= 0.4375%
<BR>
	Other expenses (legal, accounting, transfer agent, etc.) = 0.2%
<BR>
	Cumulative incentive compensation accrued and/or paid for
<BR>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;preceding 11 calendar quarters = $9 million
</P>
<H3 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 5PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 24PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Alternative 1
</H3>
<H4 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 24PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Additional Assumptions
</H4>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Investment income (including interest, dividends, fees, etc.) = 3.50%
<BR>
	Pre-incentive fee net investment income
<BR>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(investment income&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;(management fee + other expenses)) = 2.8625%
<BR>
	20.0% of cumulative net increase in net assets resulting from operations over
<BR>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;current and preceding 11 calendar quarters = $8 million
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Although our pre-incentive fee net investment income exceeds the hurdle rate of 2.0% (as shown in Alternative 3 of Example 1 above), no incentive fee is payable because 20.0% of the cumulative net increase in net assets resulting from operations over the then current and 11 preceding calendar quarters did not exceed the cumulative income and capital gains incentive fees accrued and/or paid for the preceding 11 calendar quarters.
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="WIDTH: 708PX; TEXT-INDENT:0PX; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; COLOR: BLACK; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; TEXT-DECORATION: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 12PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	16

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 8PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD">

	TABLE OF CONTENTS
</A>

<H3 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 5PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 24PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Alternative 2
</H3>
<H4 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 24PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Additional Assumptions
</H4>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Investment Income (including interest, dividends, fees, etc.) = 3.50%
<BR>
	Pre-incentive fee net investment income
<BR>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(investment income&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;(management fee + other expenses)) = 2.8625%.
<BR>
	20% of cumulative net increase in net assets resulting from operations over
<BR>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;current and preceding 11 calendar quarters = $10 million
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Because our pre-incentive fee net investment income exceeds the hurdle rate of 2.0% and because 20.0% of the cumulative net increase in net assets resulting from operations over the then current and 11 preceding calendar quarters exceeds the cumulative income and capital gains incentive fees accrued and/or paid for the preceding 11 calendar quarters, an incentive fee would be payable, as shown in Alternative 3 of Example 1 above.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 1PX">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/03/04/0001144204-16-085951_LINE.GIF" STYLE="WIDTH: 72PX; HEIGHT: 1PT">
</P>

<TR STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 1PX">

</TD>

	Represents 8.0% annualized hurdle rate.

<H2 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 5PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Example 3: Capital Gains Portion of Incentive Fee (*):
</H2>
<H3 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 5PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 24PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Alternative 1:
</H3>
<H4 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 24PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Assumptions
</H4>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Year 1:&nbsp;&nbsp;$20 million investment made in Company A (&#147;Investment A&#148;), and $30 million investment made in Company B (&#147;Investment B&#148;)
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Year 2:&nbsp;&nbsp;Investment A sold for $50 million and fair market value (&#147;FMV&#148;) of Investment B determined to be $32 million
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Year 3:&nbsp;&nbsp;FMV of Investment B determined to be $25 million
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Year 4:&nbsp;&nbsp;Investment B sold for $31 million
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	The capital gains portion of the incentive fee would be:
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Year 1:&nbsp;&nbsp;None
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Year 2:&nbsp;&nbsp;Capital gains incentive fee of $6 million&nbsp;&#151;&nbsp;($30 million realized capital gains on sale of Investment A multiplied by 20%)
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Year 3:&nbsp;&nbsp;None&nbsp;&#151;&nbsp;$5 million (20% multiplied by ($30 million cumulative capital gains less $5 million cumulative capital depreciation)) less $6 million (previous capital gains fee paid in Year 2)
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Year 4:&nbsp;&nbsp;Capital gains incentive fee of $200,000&nbsp;&#151;&nbsp;$6.2 million ($31 million cumulative realized capital gains multiplied by 20%) less $6 million (capital gains incentive fee taken in Year 2)
</P>
<H3 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 5PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 24PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Alternative 2
</H3>
<H4 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 24PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Assumptions
</H4>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Year 1:&nbsp;&nbsp;$20 million investment made in Company A (&#147;Investment A&#148;), $30 million investment made in Company B (&#147;Investment B&#148;) and $25 million investment made in Company C (&#147;Investment C&#148;)
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Year 2:&nbsp;&nbsp;Investment A sold for $50 million, FMV of Investment B determined to be $25 million and FMV of Investment C determined to be $25 million
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Year 3:&nbsp;&nbsp;FMV of Investment B determined to be $27 million and Investment C sold for $30 million
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Year 4:&nbsp;&nbsp;FMV of Investment B determined to be $35 million
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Year 5:&nbsp;&nbsp;Investment B sold for $20 million
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="WIDTH: 708PX; TEXT-INDENT:0PX; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; COLOR: BLACK; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; TEXT-DECORATION: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 12PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">

<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	The capital gains incentive fee, if any, would be:
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Year 1:&nbsp;&nbsp;None
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Year 2:&nbsp;&nbsp;$5 million capital gains incentive fee&nbsp;&#151;&nbsp;20% multiplied by $25 million ($30 million realized capital gains on Investment A less unrealized capital depreciation on Investment B)
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Year 3:&nbsp;&nbsp;$1.4 million capital gains incentive fee
<SUP>
	(1)
</SUP>
	&nbsp;&#151;&nbsp;$6.4 million (20% multiplied by $32 million ($35 million cumulative realized capital gains less $3 million unrealized capital depreciation)) less $5 million capital gains incentive fee received in Year 2
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Year 4:&nbsp;&nbsp;None
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 44PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Year 5:&nbsp;&nbsp;None&nbsp;&#151;&nbsp;$5 million (20% multiplied by $25 million (cumulative realized capital gains of $35 million less realized capital losses of $10 million)) less $6.4 million cumulative capital gains incentive fee paid in Year 2 and Year 3
<SUP>
	(2)
</SUP>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; TEXT-INDENT: 1PX">

</TD>

</TD>

</TD>

	As noted above, it is possible that the cumulative aggregate capital gains fee received by our investment advisor ($6.4 million) is effectively greater than $5 million (20% of cumulative aggregate realized capital gains less net realized capital losses or net unrealized depreciation ($25 million)).
</TD>

<H3 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 5PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Payment of Our Expenses
</H3>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	All investment professionals of MC Advisors and/or its affiliates, when and to the extent engaged in providing investment advisory and management services to us, and the compensation and routine overhead expenses of personnel allocable to these services to us, are provided and paid for by MC Advisors and not by us. We bear all other out-of-pocket costs and expenses of our operations and transactions, including, without limitation:
</P>

<H3 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 5PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Duration and Termination
</H3>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Unless terminated earlier as described below, the Investment Advisory and Management Agreement will continue in effect from year to year if approved annually by our Board or by the affirmative vote of the holders of a majority of our outstanding voting securities, and, in either case, if also approved by a majority of our directors who are not &#147;interested persons.&#148; The Investment Advisory and Management Agreement automatically terminates in the event of its assignment, as defined in the 1940 Act, by MC Advisors and may be terminated by either party without penalty upon not less than 60 days&#146; written notice to
	the other. The holders of a majority of our outstanding voting securities may also terminate the Investment Advisory and Management Agreement without penalty. See &#147;Risk Factors&nbsp;&#151;&nbsp;Risks Relating to Our Business and Structure&nbsp;&#151;&nbsp;We depend upon MC Advisors&#146; senior management for our future success, and upon its access to the investment professionals of Monroe Capital and its affiliates&#148; and &#147;Risk Factors&nbsp;&#151;&nbsp;Risks Relating to Our Business and Structure&nbsp;&#151;&nbsp;MC Advisors can resign on 60 days&#146; notice, and we may not be able to find a suitable replacement within that time, resulting in a disruption in our operations that could adversely affect our financial condition, business and results of operations.&#148;
</P>
<H3 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: ITALIC; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 5PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Indemnification
</H3>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	The Investment Advisory and Management Agreement provides that, absent willful misfeasance, bad faith or gross negligence in the performance of its duties or by reason of the reckless disregard of its duties and obligations, MC Advisors and its affiliates&#146; respective officers, directors, members, managers, stockholders and employees are entitled to indemnification from us from and against any claims or liabilities, including reasonable legal fees and other expenses reasonably incurred, arising out of or in connection with our business and operations or any action taken or omitted on our behalf pursuant to authority
	granted by the Investment Advisory and Management Agreement, except where attributable to gross negligence, willful misconduct, bad faith or reckless disregard of such person&#146;s duties under the Investment Advisory and Management Agreement.
</P>
<H2 STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: BOLD; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 5PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Administration Agreement
</H2>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Pursuant to an Administration Agreement, MC Management furnishes us with office facilities and equipment and provides us clerical, bookkeeping and record keeping and other administrative services at such facilities. Under the Administration Agreement, MC Management performs, or oversees the performance of, our required administrative services, which include, among other things, being responsible for the financial records that we are required to maintain and preparing reports to our stockholders and reports filed with the SEC. MC Management also assists us in determining and publishing our net asset value, oversees the
	preparation and filing of our tax returns, prints and disseminates reports to our stockholders and generally oversees the payment of our expenses and the performance of administrative and professional services rendered to us by others. Under the Administration Agreement, MC Management also provides managerial assistance on our behalf to those portfolio companies that have accepted our offer to provide such assistance.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-INDENT:20PX; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 3PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 4PX; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	Payments under the Administration Agreement are equal to an amount based upon our allocable portion (subject to the review and approval of our Board) of MC Management&#146;s overhead in performing its obligations under the Administration Agreement, including rent and our allocable portion of the cost of our
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="WIDTH: 708PX; TEXT-INDENT:0PX; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; FONT-SIZE: 10PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 12PT; FONT-STYLE: NORMAL; FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL; FONT-WEIGHT: NORMAL; COLOR: BLACK; TEXT-TRANSFORM: NONE; TEXT-DECORATION: NONE; PADDING-TOP: 12PT; PADDING-RIGHT: 0PT; PADDING-LEFT: 0PT; PADDING-BOTTOM: 3PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT">
	19
</P>
